<div id="review_80540809" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/80540809" />
    <a title="James Gordon" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3029633-james-gordon"><img alt="James Gordon" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/80540809?book_show_action=true">Dec 10, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="James Gordon" class="user" itemprop="url" name="James Gordon" href="/user/show/3029633-james-gordon">James Gordon</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3029633-james-gordon?shelf=ya-novels">ya-novels</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer80540809" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13192646227028781548">Nhamo lived with her dead mom’s family. Her father had abandoned her mother before Nhamo was even born. Living in a tribe who believe children belonged to the father, Nhamo was not appreciated or even treated very well by her relatives. When a cholera epidemic sweeps over the tribe, her family’s only explanation was that they were being punished for Nhamo’s presence and they decide to force her into a marriage with an older man to settle her father’s past transgressions. Her loving grandmother, </span>
  <span id="freeText13192646227028781548" style="display:none">Nhamo lived with her dead mom’s family. Her father had abandoned her mother before Nhamo was even born. Living in a tribe who believe children belonged to the father, Nhamo was not appreciated or even treated very well by her relatives. When a cholera epidemic sweeps over the tribe, her family’s only explanation was that they were being punished for Nhamo’s presence and they decide to force her into a marriage with an older man to settle her father’s past transgressions. Her loving grandmother, the only one to ever show her affection, tells Nhamo that her father’s family lives in Zimbabwe and to go find them. Her 2 day journey by boat turns into a year-long adventure and struggle to survive. In the end, she is united with her father’s family and has gained great knowledge of herself and survival. Farmer’s novel is well written and sometimes a little too long winded. Her attention to detail may discourage some readers who enjoy reading for the story more than the specifics.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13192646227028781548" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


